          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A tagged photon beam was obtained",
                "from an electron beam of energy 268 MeV. Only the",
                "photons coming with the proper secondary electrons in",
                "specified coincidence resolving time are tagged",
                "photons. Pions were produced by properly tagged",
                "photons. Particle identification was based on the",
                "comparison experimental energy loss with the Birk's",
                "formula calculations."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The differential cross section of a (gamma,pi)",
                "reaction in the lab system is dsigma/domega =",
                "Npi/(Ngamma*(Nt/cos (thetat))*DOmega), where Npi is",
                "the number of pions, Ngamma is the number of incident",
                "photons, Nt is the number of target nuclei, thetat=45",
                "degrees is the angle of the target to the beamline,",
                "and DOmega is the detector solid angle."
              ]
            }
          ],
